text:
Ro: Hey guys, it’s Ro! I’m here with my
sister Mo today!

Mo: Hey everyone, we got so many requests
to play another challenge game, so today
Mo: we’re gonna be playing, Will it Fondue?

Ro: Yum, yum, yum, yum, yum! And I went to
twitter and I asked you guys for different

Ro: suggestions of foods we should dip, and
we got so many responses.

Ro: And we had our friends pick them out,
so we have no clue what we’re gonna be dipping.
Ro: These are all gonna be a mystery to us!

Ro: If you haven’t played this game before,
you’re gonna take 1 of the mystery foods,

Ro: give it a dip, a taste, and decide, does it fondue.
Mo: Or does it fon-dont!
Ro: Oh I’m so scared!

Mo: Alright, we’ve got both our melting
pots warmed up and ready to go.

Ro: And in my pot, I’ve got light cocoa
candy melts by Wilton, and my Sister’s pot,

Ro: she has some dark chocolate heated up
in here, because Molly can’t have dairy!

Mo: Let’s find out what our first mystery
food is!
Ro: Boo-doo-da-doo!
Mo: Taquitos!?!?
Ro: Don’t we need to use these?

Mo: I’m using my hands. Ro: No, no, you
have to be fancy.

Mo: Oh… Ro: I got these fancy, OK, do you
want. Mo: I want the purple one!
Ro: You want purple.
Ro: Alright, now to dip a taquito. Mo: Here we go.
Ro: Beans doesn’t go well with that…

Ro: On 3, fondue or fon-don’t, are you ready?
Mo: OK ready.
Ro: 1, 2, 3. Both: Fon-don’t!
Mo: Oh yeah. Ro: Buh-luh-luh-luh-luh-luh-la!
Ro: UGH!

Ro: We’re off to a good start, now onto
the next one!
Ro: Uff! Wah-wah! Mo: Carrots. Ro: Carrots!

Ro: Oh! So much fashion! You guys didn’t
know this was also a fashion video.
Ro: When I dip, you dip, we dip!

Ro: Carrots don’t have that much flavor,
so that’s pretty, that’s pretty good!
Mo: Mmmhmmm. Ro: Yeah. I love carrots too!

Ro: Molly you got chocolate here, let me,
let me get it off for you!
Mo: Help me out girl, help me out!

Ro: If you had that hat on, it would have
protected you from that. Mo: I don’t think that’s true!
Ro: It’s science Molly!
Mo: 1, 2, 3. Both: Fondue!
Mo: Alright, mystery food number 3!
Mo: CHICKEN McNUGGETS!!! Yes!

Ro: What? Mo: I mean, oh yay, oh Chicken McNuggets.
Ro: Oh, it’s Chicken McNuggets.
Ro: Molly doesn’t like those at all!

Ro: OK, this is weird, just a little bit.
Mo: Oh, come on! You need to dip it!
Ro: Molly oh my gosh! Mo: This is…

Ro: I’ve heard of waffles and chicken, chicken
and waffles, but not chocolate…

Mo: Chicken and chocolate? Ro: Chicken and
chocolate.
Mo: Maybe it’s a new thing. Ro: Maybe…
Mo: I think I did too much!

Ro: Votes are in, 1, 2, 3… Mo: Fondue! Ro:
Fon-don’t!
Mo: I actually kind of liked that.
Ro: Mystery food 4, wa-da!
Mo: Oh! Ro: Oh ha-ha-ha-ha!
Mo: I’m excited for this.
Ro: Oh we use these!

Ro: These can help you pick up food, or they
can also pinch your sister’s cheeks!
Mo: Don’t you! Ro: Beep-beep-beep!
Ro: Do the dip!

Ro: Mmmmm! Mo: Has a little sweet and salty
thing, OK. Ro: Mmmhmm, mmhmm.
Mo: Ready to vote? 1, 2, 3.
Both: Fondue!

Mo: Yeah, that was pretty good. Ro: Yeah,
that was a good one!
Mo: That was a good one!

Mo: Alright, onto mystery food number 5! Ro:
Doo-doo-doo-doo!
Mo: Sushi?!?! Ro: Oh my gosh!

Ro: Oh we got a lot of different kind of rolls
here.

Ro: I’m gonna go for the shrimp. Mo: Oh
hopefully… Ro: Oh!

Ro: OK, well that’s just, well let me get
another one here and we’ll just have a little

Ro: bit of fondue teamwork! Mo: There you
go. Ro: Going on… Going on…

Ro: OK, maybe this one! Mo: Stab it, stab
it! Ro: Oh yeah there we go!

Ro: I think I did too much now, because it…
Oh! Oh my gosh! Mo: Oh no!
Ro: That’s just a fish dip! now…
Ro: Easy!
Mo: OK, here we go?

Mo: Mmm, mmm. Ro: Uh oh, uh oh, that’s not
going down!
Ro: That’s a fondue!
Both: Fon-don’t!

Mo: Do that again! Ro: Ba-la-la-la-la! Nope!
Mo: Fon-don’t do that again.
Ro: Don’t, don’t ever do that!

Ro: Please be strawberries! Please be strawberries!
Mo: Bananas!

Ro:: Bananas? Mo: Yep! Ro: That’s what you
want it to be?

Mo: Yep! Ro: I love bananas, OK, ready, please
be strawberries!
Ro: Oh my gosh, here we go.

Mo: OK, I actually love Hotdogs, so I’m
pretty curious to see how this will taste.

Ro: When Mo was little, all she would eat
was cheese, bread and hot dogs, and it’s

Ro: funny because her dairy allergy developed
later.

Mo: Just stop talking about my dairy allergy.
Ro: I just like to embarrass her!
Ro: She also has asthma!
Mo: Oh my god!

Ro: Cheers! Mo: OK, cheers! Ro: Cheers! Mo:
I feel like we’re at the campfire!
Ro: Yep! Just roasting up a little hot dog! Mo: Hot dogs on a stick... OK. Ro: Alright! All the toppings we love!
Ro: Let’s do it!

Ro: Henny! Henry is barking because he wants
these.
Ro: Henny! Do you want one of this!?!?
Mo: Fon-don’t know….
Ro: Mystery food number 7!
Mo: Pickles! Ro: Oh-ha-ha-ha-ha!

Mo: I love pickles too, they’re one of my
favorite foods, so, I’m excited for this!

Ro: I don’t know Molly, because whenever
we go to the melting pot, they, you know,

Ro: they don’t serve pickles… I just don’t
want you to be disappointed.

Mo: Maybe…. Ro: If these aren’t all you’re
thinking they’ll be!

Mo: Maybe it will be better! Maybe they don’t
put it on the menu because it’s too good!
Ro: Huh! Maybe it’s their secret menu!

Mo: I’m gonna ask next time. Ro: Hey, you
guys got pickles?!?!
Ro: Are you ready? Mo: Mmmhmmm.
Ro: Pfft! Pfft, pfft, pfft!
Ro: What kind of a pickle is that!?!?

Ro: This is a… No that’s a dill. Mo: No
that’s a sweet pickle!

Ro: No it’s sweet, a-ba-dill? Mo: That was
sweet! Ro: Is this a sweet or a dill?
Ro: 1, 2, 3… Both: Fon-don’t!
Ro: Mystery food number 8, dinner is served!
Ro: Ba-dew! Mo: OK…

Ro: Alright, we’ve got little mini Slim
Jims… Slap into a Slim Jim!
Ro: Doo-doo-doo!
Ro: Hmmmm… Mo: Hmmm.

Mo: OK, ready to vote? Ro: Yeah, I’m ready
to vote. Mo: OK, 1, 2, 3….
Ro: Fon-don’t! Mo: Fondue.

Mo: I think you can do it, I think, I think
if that’s your thing it can work.
Ro: I am hoping for marshmallows and… Candy!
Mo: Oooh! Well number 9!
Ro: Um… Mo: Fish… Sticks…

Ro: Well… Mo: Here we go. Ro: OK, don’t
knock it till you try it!
Mo: Oh! Ro: It’s almost down!
Ro: Ah, oh!
Ro: 1, 2, 3. Both: Fon-don’t!

Ro: Alright, this is our last mystery food,
number 10, and we haven’t had a lot of fondues…

Mo: No, mm-mmmm. Ro: A lot of fon-don’ts,
are you ready?

Mo: I’m ready, as long as it’s not…
Ro: She’s still hoping for pancakes!
Ro: Ah-da!

Ro: Oh my gosh! Mo: Pizza bites! Ro: They’re
pizza bites!

Ro: Definitely saving the best for last, this
is it! Mo: Here we go!
Ro: Mmmmmm, oh hot! Hot!
Ro: How’d you bite that? Is my cheese?

Ro: Come here, come here, oh you got chocolate
lipstick.
Ro: Fon-don’t. Mo: Fon…. Don’t…
Ro: Molly what was that. Da-da, da-da-da-da!

Mo: It wasn’t, it was way better than the
pickles. Ro: Yeah, oh definitely. Mo: And the sushi.

Ro: Would you serve it at restaurant Mo? Mo:
Nope, OK, fon-don’t!

Ro: Alright, that is it for the Will it Fondue
game, I hope you guys enjoyed it.

Ro: Mo has much more of an adventurous palate
than I. Mo: I just love chocolate.
Ro: That is also a factor!

Ro: Also if you’d like to learn more about
these melting pots or the candy melts that I used

Ro: today, I made 2 videos with Wilton, I’ll
put a link down below, it’s on the Wilton

Ro: channel if you want to go check those
out. And, please let us know what games you

Ro: would like to see Mo and I play next,
write us a comment, let us know what you think.

Ro: And, if you would like to see any of our
previous games, where Mo kicks my butt

Ro: in most of them, uh, we’ll have a link
up here. Mo: And up here.

Ro: Mmmhmm. Alright thanks again you guys,
bye-bye! Mo: Bye!

Ro: It’s raining strawberries! Hallelujah
it’s raining strawberries!

Ro: Oh, this is what’s up Molly! Mo: Here
we go! Ro: Molly…

Mo: Here we go, here we go! Ro: Mo, Mo, Mo,
can I get one of these?
Mo: Oh wow here we go! Ro: This is my day!
Ro: 1, 2, 3… Both: Fondue!
